Date:  0/0/1974
Source:  Australian & NZ English [TS]
Author:  SYDER & HODGETTS
Vol / Page:  916
Edition:
Quote:  A form of assent, a token word in parting, a signal to proceed with the next sequence in the operation, or, an acknowledgment that the speaker has been understood. .in 4;`Righto, then I'll leave Jack with you next trip, like you said.' 'I've got everything I wanted, I think. Righto, then, see you next week.' `Wait till I give the word you let the tray go. Righto! Now!'  `Righto! We're to leave any cleaning up till later, and load up and get back to the depot. O.K....'
Notes:  (1962-63)1974 Syder and Hodgetts Aust. and NZ English [TS] 916

